Live 2019 Election Turnout Tracker

Welcome to the Fifty Wards turnout tracker! Voters across Chicago are sharing their turnout to support citizen science.

First, vote! Then, share your precinct and Voter Number at http://bit.ly/chicagoturnout.

Live Results

As of 06:46, 25 voters in 16 wards have shared their voter number. I estimate that 350,110 people have voted across the city (95% Confidence Interval: 241,216 - 654,391). The tracker only estimates in-person votes. In February, mail-in votes represented 12% of turnout.

Maps

I use historic correlations among precincts turnout to estimate turnout in the precincts with no data yet. I simultaneously estimate (1) the overall city-wide turnout, (2) precincts over-/under-performance, and (3) the city-wide time pattern of voting.
